contentrichtext.text: {{selfref|For the Portal Quick Index, see [[WP:QI]]}} {{wiktionarypar|qi|QI}} '''[[Qi]]''', in traditional Chinese culture, is an active principle forming part of any living thing. '''Qi''' may also refer to: In '''Chinese culture''': * [[Qi (Henan)]], a minor state within China until 445 BC * [[Qi (state)|Qi (Shandong)]], a Chinese state founded 1046 BC * [[Qi (Five Dynasties)]], a small state in northwest China, 907–924 * [[Qi County, Kaifeng]], in Henan, China * [[Qi County, Hebi]], in Henan, China * [[Qi County, Shanxi]], in Jinzhong, Shanxi, China * [[Southern Qi]], a Chinese dynasty from 479 to 502 * [[Northern Qi]], a Chinese dynasty from 550 to 577 * [[Qi (surname)]] * [[Qi]] or chi (氣), "energy force" in Chinese culture In '''other uses''': * ''[[QI]]'' (Quite Interesting), a BBC television programme * Quartz Iodine, now called a [[Halogen lamp]] * [[Qi Card]], the Iraqi national credit Card * "[[Q.I]]", a song by Mylène Farmer from ''Avant que l'ombre...'' * [[Qi hardware]] open hardware project * [[Qi (programming language)]] * [[QueryInterface]], a function within IUnknown * [[Cimber Air]]'s IATA designator * [[Qimonda]]'s NYSE symbol * ''QI: The Quest for Intelligence'', a book by [[Kevin Warwick]] * [[ATCvet code QI]] ''Immunologicals'', a section of the Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical Classification System for veterinary medicinal products * [[Qi (inductive power standard)]], the name of an interface specification published by the Wireless Power Consortium '''People''': * [[Qi of Xia]], the second king (reigned 2146–2117 BC) of the Xia Dynasty * [[Houji]], or Qi, an ancestor of the Chinese Zhou dynasty * [[Shu Qi]] (born 1976), a Taiwanese actress * [[Qi Jingyi]] (1656–1719), a Chinese Sufi master ==See also== * [[KI (disambiguation)]] * [[Key (disambiguation)]] * [[Chi (disambiguation)]] {{disambig}} [[Category:Given names]] [[Category:Surnames]]
